metadata.name: Turtledum of Honolua Bay
metadata.description:
Turtledum of Honolua Bay, once helped the Picaroons find buried treasure whilst laying eggs on the beach during The Royal Picaroons era.

Rackham of Port Royal, tattooed the Picaroon flag on their starboard scute as thanks. 

Part of the Testudines Order of reptiles, they are fond of telling everyone “All Tortoises are Turtles”...as they swim the seven seas in search of their long lost twin Turtledee.

They enjoy watching surfboards splinter into the coral reefs of Honolua Bay and dream of opening a Slow Food Service Restaurant with Picaroon Cook, Enriquez of Capetown.
